Text.Value: Chk - more time wasted. If only you feared the ghaik parasite half as much as you fear the dark.
Leave.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Has  quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: Whatever. I'm not afraid of a few shadows.
Of course I do. Why do you ask?
One of them pixie-lamps. If you're headin' to Moonrise, you won't last without it.
Afraid of the dark, are we? Very well - let us save Nere, if we must.

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Does not have quest for Moonrise towers

Text.Value: Sounds like bad news. I'd just as soon get that Moonlantern off Nere.
We need to press on. Nere is a distraction.
There we have it. Let 'Operation Free Nere' commence.
Must be the shadow curse. We'll need Nere's lantern if we want to get through it.
You just want me to die in a cursed cloud so you can take my boots. Finally, the plot revealed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Kidding but grim, not too much levity.

Text.Value: Let's just hope you're right. Otherwise we're just aiding the enemy.
I ask 'cause you ain't gettin' far without one of them pixie-lamps.
A stab in the dark it is...
'Death-dark' doesn't sound very inviting. Can't say I fancy our chances without freeing Nere and getting that Moonlantern.
'Death-dark'? Sounds like my kind of thing. What is it?
The surface is within reach. But it may be foolish to press on before finding this Nere.
I'm one of the reasons people fear the shadows, but even I'd rather investigate this Moonlantern before going to the surface.
Agreed. Next stop: Nere.
A Moonlantern? What's that?
I've seen much death already... I'll be careful.
'Death-dark'? What are you talking about?
Thanks for sharing. I'll keep it in mind.
That Moonlantern is key to our survival. And that means freeing Nere.
So we're going up there without the lantern? I hope you know what you're doing.
He speaks of the shadow curse. Moonrise must be close, but it would be foolish to press on before seeking out this Nere.
The shadow curse. We'll need that Moonlantern from Nere to survive the journey to Moonrise Towers.
Leave.
No. So what?
My thoughts exactly.
That Moonlantern is key to our survival. And that means freeing Nere.
Sounds like the shadow curse. We must be getting close to Moonrise. Perhaps we should seek out this Nere while we can, though.
Forward, then. No curse will keep me from purification.
Moonrise Towers holds the answers we seek. Curse or not, we can't turn back now.
We were warned about the curse. Can't say I fancy our chances without a Moonlantern.
No surprises that there's danger ahead, but we're getting closer. Perhaps we should seek out Nere while we can, though.
You daft? It's there in the name. Shadows up there, black as the Lowerdark. A few sniffs could fell an ogre.
Good. After all we've been through, this is hardly the time to falter.

EditorData.NodeContext: Approving of the player's decision to press onwards through danger to their goal

Text.Value: If the cure's in Moonrise, we should go, Nere and his lantern be damned. After all, 'shadows' will be the least of our worries if we start to turn.
Shit. You got one of Nere's Moonlanterns, jargh?
Excellent. The less time I have to spend with these underdwarves, the better.
Excellent. The less time I have to spend with these underdwarves, the better. Present company excluded, of course.
Top-lands are clogged with the death-dark, choke you in no time.
Go on, get some air. But don't go cursing me if that shadow-shit snuffs you.
Well, damn. Then go on up, take a stroll. Long as you keep your lips off our ale, I don't give two shits.
I'm not so keen on taking a shadow-nap, myself. We need to free Nere and get that Moonlantern.
So if you're headin' Moonrise-way, you ain't gettin' far. Not without one of Nere's pixie-lamps.

Synopsis: Player clicks on elevator leading to the shadow-cursed lands. Nearby duergar butt in to let you know you don't look like you're in any shape to go up there. The land is cursed, and you need a moonlantern. Plays only once.
